An East London school shut its doors on Tuesday after a teacher tested positive for Covid-19. The teacher from Qaqamba Senior Secondary School in Duncan Village had interacted with his colleagues and pupils. DispatchLIVE understands that the teacher had been working since the reopening of schools before he apparently fell sick about a week ago. "Today the school has received its first confirmation of a teacher who tested positive for Covid-19," reads a letter from principal K.K Ngcetane and SGB chair Rev D.C Blacky. "In consultation with SGB, the school management has decided to temporarily close the school from 08 July 2020 to 10 July 2020.This is to allow deep cleaning and disinfection of the school." Provincial education spokesperson Loyiso Pulumani confirmed the school was temporarily closed. In the public interest, most of our coronavirus news isn’t behind our paywall, and is free to read. To support our mission of delivering award-winning, independent local news, subscribe from as little as R45 per month by clicking here.